article.headline: Montana St. 76, Cal Poly-SLO 72
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Marquis Navarre scored 18 points, Branden Johnson added 16 and Montana State rallied in the final minutes to defeat Cal Poly 76-72 Monday night. After Lorenzo Keeler's jumper put the Mustangs ahead 72-69 with 3 minutes remaining, the Bobcats (7-4) responded with a 7-0 run that gave them their first lead and third straight victory. Bobby Howard's jumper put Montana State up 73-72 with 1:46 to play, and Erik Rush hit three free throws to close the scoring. Will Donahue led Cal Poly (3-7) with 19 points and 13 rebounds, his fifth double-double of the season. The Mustangs led by as many as nine and held a 35-33 advantage at halftime after the Bobcats closed the half on a 10-5 run. Montana State's rally was fueled by 57.7 percent shooting in the second half.
